````# üí† GlassIris.v1 ‚Äì 3D CSS UI Style System ## Overview GlassIris.v1 is the default 3D CSS GUI theme for all CrystalSeed projects. It emphasizes iridescent, frameless, glass-like panels with depth, glow, and clarity ‚Äî designed to feel weightless yet precise, and compatible with Shopify frontends. --- ## üß± Core Principles - **Frameless**: No solid boxes or harsh borders. All edges use glow, shadow, or blur for distinction. - **Iridescent Accents**: Gradients and edge glows using purples, blues, teals, and pinks. - **Depth Aware**: All elements feel layered or float with perspective, parallax, or blur. - **3D Typography**: Letters/numbers appear bevelled or shadow-layered to evoke depth. - **Performance-Safe**: Built in pure CSS with optional R3F overlays. Shopify-compliant. - **Accessibility First**: All glow and transparency passes WCAG contrast. --- ## üé® Color Tokens | Token | Value | |-------|-------| | --glassiris-bg | `rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05)` | | --glassiris-glow | `linear-gradient(135deg, #6ee7b7, #9333ea, #3b82f6)` | | --glassiris-shadow | `rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15)` | | --glassiris-border | `1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1)` | | --glassiris-text | `#f3f4f6` | --- ## üß© Components ### üî≤ Panels ```css .glass-panel { background: var(--glassiris-bg); border-radius: 2rem; border: var(--glassiris-border); box-shadow: 0 4px 24px var(--glassiris-shadow); backdrop-filter: blur(12px); -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px); }````

import { createContext, useContext, useState, ReactNode } from "react";

interface ThemeContextType {

 theme: string;

 setTheme: (theme: string) \=\> void;

}

const ThemeContext \= createContext\<ThemeContextType | undefined\>(undefined);

export function useGlassIrisTheme() {

 const context \= useContext(ThemeContext);

 if (\!context) {

   throw new Error("useGlassIrisTheme must be used within a GlassIrisProvider");

 }

 return context;

}

interface GlassIrisProviderProps {

 children: ReactNode;

 defaultTheme?: string;

}

export function GlassIrisProvider({ children, defaultTheme \= "glassiris" }: GlassIrisProviderProps) {

 const \[theme, setTheme\] \= useState(defaultTheme);

 return (

   \<ThemeContext.Provider value\={{ theme, setTheme }}\>

     \<div className\={\`theme-${theme}\`}\>{children}\</div\>

   \</ThemeContext.Provider\>

 );

}

// Example usage in a Hydrogen component:

// \<GlassIrisProvider\>

//   \<YourApp /\>

// \</GlassIrisProvider\>
